@post_election
on-arrival: {!
// set congress proportion to votes
Q.d66_r = Q.d66_votes;
Q.cda_r = Q.cda_votes;
Q.gl_r = Q.gl_votes;
Q.pvda_r = Q.pvda_votes;
Q.vvd_r = Q.vvd_votes;
Q.ja21_r = Q.ja21_votes;
Q.pvv_r = Q.pvv_votes;
Q.other_r = Q.other_votes;

// The largest party can only be the pvv or the d66.
Q.largest_party = 'd66';
if (Q.pvv_r >= Q.d66_r && Q.pvv_r >= Q.gl_r) {
    Q.largest_party = 'pvv';
}
if (Q.gl_r >= Q.d66_r && Q.gl_r >= Q.pvv_r) {
    Q.largest_party = 'gl';
}

// coalitions
Q.weimar_coalition = Q.d66_r + Q.pvda_r + Q.cda_r - 3;
Q.grand_coalition = Q.d66_r + Q.pvda_r + Q.cda_r + Q.vvd_r;
Q.bourgeois_coalition = Q.pvda_r + Q.cda_r + Q.vvd_r + Q.other_r;
Q.center_right_coalition = Q.cda_r + Q.pvda_r + Q.vvd_r + Q.other_r + Q.ja21_r;
Q.right_coalition = Q.cda_r + Q.vvd_r + Q.other_r + Q.ja21_r;
Q.far_right_coalition = Q.ja21_r + Q.pvv_r;
Q.left_coalition = Q.d66_r + Q.gl_r;
// this is an absurd concept lol
Q.united_front_coalition = Q.d66_r + Q.gl_r + Q.cda_r + Q.pvda_r - 3;
Q.anti_democratic_coalition = Q.gl_r + Q.pvv_r;
// aka everyone except nacdai, gl, ja21
Q.neo_weimar_coalition = Q.d66_r + Q.pvda_r + Q.cda_r + Q.vvd_r + Q.other_r;
!}

The electoral system is essentially proportional, with the proportion of Reichstag seats roughly equal to the proportion of votes.
 
**Election results:**

# 1928: 30, 1930: 25, 1932: 22
d66: [+ d66_r +]

# 1928: 15, 1930: 15, 1932: 
cda + BVP: [+ cda_r +]

# 1928: 10, 1930: 13
gl: [+ gl_r +]

# 1928: 5, 1930: 4 (as DstP)
pvda: [+ pvda_r +]

# 1928: 9, 1930: 5
vvd: [+ vvd_r +]

# 1928: 14, 1930: 7
ja21: [+ ja21_r +]

# 1928: 3, 1930: 18
pvv: [+ pvv_r +]

# 1928: 9, 1930: 10
Other: [+ other_r +]

**Potential coalitions:**

Weimar Coalition (d66 + cda + pvda): [+ weimar_coalition +]

Grand Coalition (d66 + cda + BVP + pvda + vvd): [+ grand_coalition +]

Bourgeois Coalition (cda + BVP + pvda + vvd + Others): [+ bourgeois_coalition +]

Right-wing Coalition (cda + BVP + vvd + Others + ja21): [+ right_coalition +]

